    <fr:title text="Sheaves relative to a cover set">Sheaves relative to a cover set</fr:title>
    <fr:taxon>Definition</fr:taxon>
    <fr:meta name="source">Definition 2.4, <fr:link href="/jung-moshier-vickers-2008/" title="Presenting dcpos and dcpo algebras" uri="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jung-moshier-vickers-2008/" display-uri="jung-moshier-vickers-2008" type="local">[jung-moshier-vickers-2008]</fr:link></fr:meta>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex> be a preorder equipped with a cover set <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex>. A <html:em><fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[C]]></fr:tex>-sheaf</html:em> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[I]]></fr:tex> is defined to be a downward-closed subset of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex> that is closed under all covers in the sense that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[U\subseteq  I]]></fr:tex> implies <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\in  I]]></fr:tex> for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a\lhd _C U]]></fr:tex>.</html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
